REMU: bootdone_service — fast-path to FW_BOOT_DONE on CL0

REMU is a purely functional emulator and does not model the silicon blocks
that bootdone_task consults after pf_bootdone_status converges (SPI sysinfo
flash, CMRT-backed RoT handshake via request_to_cmrt, DVFS HW_CFG voltage,
rl_sysinfo_broadcast over HBM mailboxes, CL3 dedicated-flash sync over IPM).
In QEMU, these either return -EBUSY from a synchronous SPI stub or block
forever on a mailbox wait, so bootdone_task never reaches
bootdone_notify_to_host(PCIE_PF) — which is precisely what the host kmd
polls for (FW_BOOT_DONE = 0xFB0D in ISSR[4] on the PF mailbox).

Add a REMU_FAST_BOOTDONE shortcut that, on CL0 and once every chiplet's
set_chiplet_bootdone_status(cl_id) has flagged PF bootdone-mask convergence,
skips all the unmodelled phases and emits the host notification directly.
CL1/2/3 still fall through to the hils_reg_base setup they need.

This patch lives under cli/fw-patches/ and is auto-applied by
./remucli fw-build so it cannot be silently lost on a submodule refresh.

diff --git a/osl/FreeRTOS/Source/services/bootdone_service/bootdone_service.c b/osl/FreeRTOS/Source/services/bootdone_service/bootdone_service.c
index 94a870b67..c659843d6 100644
--- a/osl/FreeRTOS/Source/services/bootdone_service/bootdone_service.c
+++ b/osl/FreeRTOS/Source/services/bootdone_service/bootdone_service.c
@@ -66,6 +66,25 @@ REGISTER_FILE_NUM(LOG_ID_BOOTDONE_TASK);
 #define FW_LOAD_MASK				0x0000ffff
 #define FW_BOOT_DONE				0xFB0D	/* D2H */
 
+/*
+ * REMU_FAST_BOOTDONE — shortcut for the REMU functional emulator.
+ *
+ * The late-boot phases gated by bootdone_task (SPI sysinfo retrieval, RoT
+ * handshake via request_to_cmrt, DVFS voltage request, rl_sysinfo_broadcast,
+ * CL3 FW sync over IPM) rely on silicon blocks REMU does not model. Running
+ * them inside QEMU either returns -EBUSY from a synchronous SPI stub or
+ * blocks forever on a mailbox wait, preventing bootdone_task from ever
+ * reaching bootdone_notify_to_host(PCIE_PF).
+ *
+ * When REMU_FAST_BOOTDONE is defined (always, in-tree, carried as a
+ * versioned patch under cli/fw-patches/), CL0 skips directly from the
+ * pf_bootdone_status poll (which succeeds because set_chiplet_bootdone_status
+ * is called on every chiplet) to bootdone_notify_to_host(PCIE_PF), emitting
+ * FW_BOOT_DONE to ISSR[4] on the PF mailbox. This is what the host-side kmd
+ * actually polls for, so for REMU's Phase 1 + Phase 2 scope it is sufficient.
+ */
+#define REMU_FAST_BOOTDONE
+
 void update_sw_ver_info(bool secureboot_done)
 {
 	int ret = RL_ERROR;
@@ -514,6 +533,20 @@ void bootdone_task(void *param)
 				goto ret;
 			}
 		}
+#ifdef REMU_FAST_BOOTDONE
+		/*
+		 * REMU: skip the unmodelled late-boot phases (SPI sysinfo /
+		 * RoT request_to_cmrt / DVFS / rl_sysinfo_broadcast / CL3 FW
+		 * sync over IPM) and jump straight to notifying the host.
+		 * See the REMU_FAST_BOOTDONE block comment at the top of this
+		 * file for the rationale.
+		 */
+		printf("REMU: fast bootdone path\r\n");
+		RLOG_DBG("REMU: fast bootdone path\r\n");
+		bootdone_notify_to_host(PCIE_PF);
+		rl_bootstat_set_boot_done();
+		goto ret;
+#endif
 #if defined(CP_SERVICE_ENABLED) && !defined(CP_ENABLE_SANITY)
 		/* Poll hils_check_product_info_ready until it returns RL_OK for 3 seconds */
 		{
